{"session_id":"svc-1778753260177234562","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-14T10:07:41.208681416Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"opus","sticky":{"key_present":true,"bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"requested_harness":"claude","resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"request_harness","requested_model":"opus","resolved_model":"opus","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-701cdf39-20260514T100704-ca70df67","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children once more; third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260514T100704-ca70df67/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a success. Do not mix implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260514T100704-ca70df67/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260514T100704-ca70df67/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;To request orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260514T100704-ca70df67/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260514T100704-ca70df67/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-701cdf39\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eworker: workerprobe emits periodic worker.heartbeat events with fail-open when no server\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;The workerprobe mirrors loop events via `TeeJSONL`, so during a long-running attempt with no intermediate loop event, the server\u0026#39;s `last_event_at` stays at claim time. The server cannot distinguish an actively-working worker from a silent/stale one. The new periodic liveness mechanism must also fail open: when no server address is configured or the server refuses connections, work must continue without errors, status churn, new failure states, or cooldowns.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;- `cli/internal/agent/work/heartbeat.go:13-35` ticks but emits no event to the probe.\u0026#xA;- `cli/internal/agent/workerprobe/probe.go:209-228` `RecordEvent` already best-effort posts to `/api/workers/\u0026lt;id\u0026gt;/event` when connected and buffers when not — but nobody calls it for heartbeat-cadence events.\u0026#xA;- `cli/internal/server/worker_ingest.go:110-120` updates `last_event_at` only when `/api/workers/\u0026lt;id\u0026gt;/event` receives an event.\u0026#xA;- `cli/cmd/execute_loop_shared.go:174-186` connects the probe but only `TeeJSONL`-mirrored loop events flow through it.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;Wire a probe-aware liveness emitter into the `WithHeartbeat` tick: on each tick, when a `*workerprobe.Probe` (or a minimal `RecordEvent`-shaped interface) is available, call `probe.RecordEvent(Event{Kind: \u0026#34;worker.heartbeat\u0026#34;, BeadID: ..., AttemptID: ..., Body: \u0026lt;small JSON\u0026gt;})`. The body should be a compact envelope (worker_id, current_bead, attempt_id, phase, ts) — enough to refresh `last_event_at` server-side and provide minimal context. `RecordEvent` is already non-blocking and best-effort. When no addr / connection refused / no probe, the call must be silent (a single debug-level log line is acceptable) and must not propagate errors to the attempt path.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Do not change the probe\u0026#39;s connection lifecycle, register/backfill behavior, or backoff/jitter constants.\u0026#xA;- Do not add a new server endpoint; reuse the existing `/api/workers/\u0026lt;id\u0026gt;/event` path.\u0026#xA;- Do not write the local sidecar (covered by sibling bead ddx-1be8df2b).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Parent: ddx-a3589116. Dependencies: none (independent of ddx-1be8df2b — the two together complete the parent).\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. Add `TestWorkerProbe_PeriodicHeartbeatRefreshesServerLastEventAt` (under `cli/internal/agent/workerprobe/...` or `cli/internal/server/...`): with a reachable httptest server, a simulated long-running attempt with a short heartbeat tick produces multiple `worker.heartbeat` POSTs to `/api/workers/\u0026lt;id\u0026gt;/event`; the server-derived `last_event_at` (per `worker_ingest.go:110-120`) advances between claim and the eventual `bead.result`.\u0026#xA;2. Add `TestWorkerProbe_ServerUnavailableDoesNotBlockWork`: with `AddrFunc` returning \u0026#34;\u0026#34; or a connection-refused server, the same heartbeat path produces no errors propagated to the attempt; no new failure status, cooldown, or stop is introduced; the attempt completes normally.\u0026#xA;3. `cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/workerprobe/... ./internal/agent/work/... ./internal/server/... -run \u0026#34;TestWorkerProbe_PeriodicHeartbeatRefreshesServerLastEventAt|TestWorkerProbe_ServerUnavailableDoesNotBlockWork\u0026#34; -count=1` green.\u0026#xA;4. `lefthook run pre-commit passes`.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003earea:agent, area:server, area:work, kind:bug, phase:build, reliability\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-a3589116\" spec-id=\"FEAT-006\" base-rev=\"c23d1fa52ae04d6ac726b7264608f17892b3efc0\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260514T100704-ca70df67\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"FEAT-006\" path=\"docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-006-agent-service.md\"\u003eFeature: DDx Consumer of the Fizeau Execution Contract\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260514T100704-ca70df67","base_rev":"c23d1fa52ae04d6ac726b7264608f17892b3efc0","bead_id":"ddx-701cdf39","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260514T100704-ca70df67","correlation_id":"ddx-701cdf39:20260514T100704-ca70df67","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260514T100704-ca70df67/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"038da68a96fe2956b736d3464dd7cd99f86ecc7676648742ab797fb174378b1a","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-e7abc956","worker_id":""}}}
